          <strong>Buffalo Business Tip:</strong> The NY Workers' Compensation Board actively monitors compliance. Don't risk your business—get covered today. We can provide same-day certificates for urgent needs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Buffalo Workers' Comp Questions</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Common questions from Western New York employers
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            How much does workers' comp cost for Buffalo businesses?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            For Buffalo employers, workers' comp costs typically range from <strong>$1-$2 per $100 of payroll</strong> for low-risk businesses (offices, retail) to <strong>$5-$15 per $100</strong> for high-risk industries (construction, manufacturing). Your exact rate depends on your industry classification, payroll, and claims history. Buffalo-specific factors like winter weather-related claims can also impact rates for outdoor workers.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Do I need workers' comp for seasonal employees in Buffalo?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. In New York, <strong>all employees must be covered</strong> from their first day of work, including seasonal, part-time, and temporary workers. This is especially important for Buffalo businesses that hire seasonal staff for winter operations (snow removal, holiday events) or summer work (construction, waterfront activities).
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Are lake-effect weather injuries covered?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. Workers' compensation covers injuries from <strong>slips on ice, snow removal accidents, and weather-related incidents</strong> during work. Given Buffalo's legendary lake-effect snow (often exceeding 90+ inches), it's crucial your policy properly classifies outdoor workers and snow removal operations to ensure adequate coverage.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Does coverage extend to Canadian border crossings?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Your NY workers' comp policy covers employees working in New York. For employees who regularly cross into Canada for work, you may need <strong>additional coverage</strong>. Contact us to discuss cross-border insurance options for Buffalo businesses operating near the Peace Bridge.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            How quickly can I get a certificate of insurance?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            PCFG Insurance can often provide <strong>same-day certificates of insurance</strong> for Buffalo businesses. This is critical when you need proof of coverage for contracts, construction permits, or vendor requirements. We understand Western NY businesses need fast service—contact us by 2 PM for same-day issuance.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Ready to protect your Buffalo business?</p>
        <a href="#quote-form" class="inline-block bg-navy-600 hover:bg-navy-700 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-md font-semibold transition-colors duration-200">
          Get Your Free Buffalo Quote
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

